# calimocho — License Summary

> **TL;DR**: calimocho is free for personal and other non-commercial use.
> You may NOT sell it, charge for support around it, or include it in a
> paid product. This is because Apple's Game Porting Toolkit license
> (which governs the bundled `D3DMetal.framework`) restricts distribution
> to non-commercial purposes.

## Calimocho's own scripts and docs

The shell scripts, install logic, build automation, and documentation in this
repository are licensed under the **GNU Lesser General Public License
version 2.1 or later** (LGPL-2.1-or-later) — the same license as Wine itself.

See https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-2.1.html for the canonical text.

## Bundled dependencies

| Component | Source | License |
|---|---|---|
| **Wine 11.0** | https://www.winehq.org | LGPL-2.1-or-later |
| **CodeWeavers Wine patches** | https://media.codeweavers.com/pub/crossover/source/ | LGPL-2.1-or-later |
| **vkd3d** | https://gitlab.winehq.org/wine/vkd3d | LGPL-2.1-or-later |
| **DXVK** *(v0.6+)* | https://github.com/doitsujin/dxvk | zlib license |
| **MoltenVK** | https://github.com/KhronosGroup/MoltenVK | Apache 2.0 |
| **Apple D3DMetal.framework** | Apple Game Porting Toolkit 3 | **Apple GPTK SLA** ⚠️ |
| **Apple /redist components** | Same | **Apple GPTK SLA** ⚠️ |
| **xxHash** *(inside D3DMetal)* | https://github.com/Cyan4973/xxHash | BSD-2-Clause |

Full Apple GPTK License Agreement is reproduced verbatim in
`THIRDPARTY/Apple-GPTK/LICENSE.rtf` at build time.

## ⚠️ The non-commercial restriction (Apple GPTK SLA §2A iii + §2C)

Apple grants a non-commercial, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to
install, use, and distribute D3DMetal and Redistributables.
The Framework may be distributed *separately* from the rest of GPTK.
This is what makes calimocho legal.

The license is **strictly non-commercial**.

You may NOT:
- ❌ Sell calimocho or any product/service incorporating it
- ❌ Charge for technical support around calimocho
- ❌ Bundle it in a paid app, subscription, or hosted service
- ❌ Use it in a service-bureau, time-sharing, or paid hosted-gaming offering
- ❌ Modify, decompile, or reverse-engineer the D3DMetal binary

You MAY:
- ✅ Use it personally for free on your own Mac
- ✅ Share with family, friends, colleagues at no charge
- ✅ Redistribute through forks, mirrors, free package managers
- ✅ Accept donations (GitHub Sponsors / Patreon) to maintain the project
- ✅ Use it in classroom / research / educational contexts

## Why CrossOver can charge for the same components

CodeWeavers has a separate commercial agreement with Apple (they're named on
Apple's GPTK page as a recommended commercial solution). That contract is
private; we can't replicate it.

If you can afford [CrossOver](https://www.codeweavers.com/crossover) ($74/yr),
buying it is the right way to fund the people whose work makes calimocho
possible.

